<font color="#FF0000">THANKS, TOM! AND 1 MORE POINT:</font><br>
<tt>Sat Nov 22 10:18:07 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Thanks, Tom!<br><br>
I always enjoy your perspective, my brother of choice!<br><br>
One other point that I need to make:<br><br>
Many of us have struggled to rise above the cess pool that took up residence in our minds many years ago because of the Vietnam War. Some of us have clawed our way a little more out of it than others, some of us clawed our way out in some things, but are still stuck in it in others.<br><br>
What is important and must be acknowledged is that we know it and we really work hard at fixing ourselves! There are many kind, generous, caring people who help us, and it is to them we are indebted and to only them we listen.<br><br>
To those who wish to diminish our worth to ourselves and our country, to damage our self-esteem, to display their peacock rainbow of bigotry, hatred and fear towards us, impune our dignity, and otherwise attempt to push us down into the inferno of constant emotional pain out of which we continue to struggle to rise, GO TO HELL! <br><br>
Art,<br><br>
A Vietnam Veteran, and very proud of it! 
